## Structure

Each subdirectory is a self-contained Odoo module. Modules live at the
repository root — one folder per module, matching the standard
`{{ '{addon}/__manifest__.py' }}` layout.

## Install

Clone next to your other Odoo addons paths and add this directory to
`--addons-path`:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{ org_slug }}/{{ repo_slug }}.git
odoo-bin -c odoo.conf --addons-path=/path/to/odoo/addons,/path/to/{{ repo_slug }}
```

Per-module Python requirements live in each module's `requirements.txt` (if
any). Install the aggregate with:

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Development

```bash
pip install pre-commit
pre-commit install
pre-commit run --all-files
```

CI runs the same hooks plus the Odoo test matrix on every PR
(`.github/workflows/`).

## License

Modules default to `{{ default_license }}`. Per-module license is declared in
each `__manifest__.py`.

